President Obama has declared a major disaster in the State of New Jersey and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts following a snowstorm that occurred in December 2009. The funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and replacement in several counties. Additionally, federal funding will support emergency protective measures and hazard mitigation measures throughout the state. Stephen M. DeBlasio Sr. has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for recovery operations in the affected area, and further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact FEMA at (202) 646-3272.